thanks-thank:
{{Doc-actionlink}}
A link to thank another user. This appears next to messages such as {{msg-mw|editundo}} and {{msg-mw|rollbacklink}} and should be translated in a similar fashion.
For languages that need it, the gender of each of the thanked and thanking users is available.
{{Identical|Thank}} 
* $1 - The user that is thanking
* $2 - The user that is thanked

echo-category-title-edit-thank:
This is a short title for the notification category.

Used as <code>$1</code> in {{msg-mw|Echo-dismiss-message}} and as <code>$2</code> in {{msg-mw|Echo-email-batch-category-header}}
{{Related|Echo-category-title}}
{{Identical|Thank}}

log-show-hide-thanks:
Shown on [[Special:Log]] as a link to show/hide thanks log entries. (Hidden by default)
* $1 - one of {{msg-mw|Show}} or {{msg-mw|Hide}}
{{Related|Log-show-hide}}

thanks-confirmation-special:
A confirmation message shown on [[Special:Thanks]] to make sure the user wants to send thanks for an edit.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Flow-thanks-confirmation-special}}
* {{msg-mw|Thanks-confirmation2}}

flow-thanks-confirmation-special:
A confirmation message shown on [[Special:Thanks]] to make sure the user wants to send thanks for a comment.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Thanks-confirmation-special}}

